      • getAttendantId

        public int getAttendantId()
        Returns:
        Associated Attendant ID.
        Note : Reserved for future use. Always set to -1.

      • getPumpNumber

        public int getPumpNumber()
        Returns:
        Pump number if the reader was a pump, or can be mapped to a logical pump based on Enabler Configuration. Otherwise returns -1.

      • getTagData

        public java.lang.String getTagData()
        Returns:
        Tag Data - the binary data from the tag presented in a hexidecimal string format.

      • getTagId

        public int getTagId()
        Returns:
        Tag Id.
        Note : Reserved for future use. Always set to -1.

      • getTagPresent

        public java.lang.Boolean getTagPresent()
        Returns:
        True If Tag is in proximity to the reader (present).
        False If tag has been removed from reader - in this case TagData will be an empty string.
        Tag removed events are fired for some types of readers.

      • getTagReaderID

        public int getTagReaderID()
        Returns:
        Id of the Reader where tag has been presented.
        For integrated Pump Tagging this will be the ID of the pump in the database (Pumps.Pump_ID).
        For Standalone Tag readers this will be the ID of the reader setup in the database (Tag_Reader.Tag_Reader_ID).
